				<p><bibl><ptr target="bib:ASB"/><citedRange>1912: 12 §37</citedRange></bibl> reports the inscription in Bodawpaya’s Amarapura collection and relates correspondence with Blagden. Mention is also made in <bibl><ptr target="bib:ASB"/><citedRange>1913: 21-2</citedRange></bibl>. It is also included as #5 in the list of known Pyu inscriptions in <bibl><ptr target="bib:Blagden1913-1914_01"/><citedRange>127 (5)</citedRange></bibl>. <bibl><ptr target="bib:SeinWin2016_01"/><citedRange>127-30</citedRange></bibl> provides the only transliteration (in Burmese script). </p>
